[13:30 - 17:00] Infrastructure and Jenkins Setup (DevOps)
Task: Provision an EC2 instance and install Jenkins for continuous integration.
13:30 - 14:15 | EC2 Provisioning:
Launched a new Amazon Linux 2 EC2 instance (t2.medium) in the designated VPC subnet.
Configured Security Group to allow inbound traffic on SSH (Port 22), HTTP (Port 80), and Jenkins (Port 8080).
14:15 - 15:30 | Java & Dependencies:
SSHed into the instance.
Updated the system packages: sudo yum update -y.
Installed Java Development Kit (JDK 11), as required by the Jenkins version: sudo yum install java-11-amazon-corretto -y.
15:30 - 16:45 | Jenkins Installation:
Imported the Jenkins GPG key and added the Jenkins repository to the system sources.
Installed Jenkins using sudo yum install jenkins.
Started the Jenkins service: sudo systemctl start jenkins.
Ensured Jenkins is set to run on boot: sudo systemctl enable jenkins.
